e \"hung onto him\" could relate to contamination.","dimension":13,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.10006,0.14463,0.13009,0.097165,0.088791,0.082469,0.07404,0.078415,0.058529,0.055859,0.046769,0.043186],"unified_progress":[0.10414,0.09725,0.095485,0.09166,0.090573,0.091034,0.084837,0.09542,0.072754,0.069512,0.058455,0.04888]},{"section":9,"text":"The mention of cleaning and not feeling satisfied even after cleaning once makes me think of obsessive-compulsive behaviors.","dimension":13,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.077473,0.11813,0.10826,0.09809,0.091456,0.088321,0.082382,0.082569,0.070799,0.070036,0.058954,0.053532],"unified_progress":[0.088379,0.088877,0.088326,0.088929,0.08902,0.090439,0.086908,0.091488,0.081154,0.080654,0.068738,0.057088]},{"section":10,"text":"The key points are the recurrent intrusive thoughts about contamination (even after cleaning) and the compulsion to clean despite knowing it's irrational.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.075669,0.12006,0.10483,0.091917,0.086662,0.087329,0.081452,0.084617,0.072687,0.071505,0.062961,0.060315],"unified_progress":[0.081343,0.091748,0.087806,0.086411,0.085901,0.089349,0.085411,0.090941,0.082394,0.081145,0.073407,0.064145]},{"section":11,"text":"That's classic OCD.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049012,0.088939,0.10655,0.10855,0.09978,0.087221,0.08475,0.079341,0.074673,0.084254,0.067249,0.069682],"unified_progress":[0.051594,0.069407,0.078582,0.092549,0.092386,0.091126,0.093178,0.090453,0.087613,0.09712,0.082517,0.073476]},{"section":12,"text":"The \"diy street\" might be a mistranslation or typo for \"dirty street\" or something similar.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.31719,0.05201,0.05213,0.061375,0.062824,0.065085,0.061441,0.069092,0.070927,0.066589,0.07055,0.050788],"unified_progress":[0.2047,0.081733,0.062884,0.062573,0.073229,0.073856,0.094804,0.082343,0.08041,0.065712,0.061574,0.056184]},{"section":13,"text":"The patient's awareness that the thought is unfounded but still feeling compelled to act on it fits OCD criteria.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.089068,0.18341,0.060674,0.090875,0.081769,0.089912,0.076476,0.072444,0.068747,0.065079,0.061443,0.060103],"unified_progress":[0.10481,0.12176,0.064247,0.086117,0.081785,0.093609,0.081177,0.079069,0.077043,0.074447,0.071109,0.064822]},{"section":14,"text":"Other possibilities could be contamination fears in anxiety disorders, but OCD is more specific here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041909,0.080599,0.0955,0.096178,0.094972,0.08975,0.089975,0.086534,0.083243,0.085046,0.076966,0.079328],"unified_progress":[0.039969,0.065389,0.076962,0.088102,0.089121,0.090716,0.092472,0.091745,0.092001,0.096076,0.091137,0.086311]},{"section":15,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis is obsessive-compulsive disorder.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038129,0.062313,0.067826,0.07305,0.076925,0.079298,0.083294,0.086064,0.089797,0.094058,0.10065,0.14859],"unified_progress":[0.039817,0.040695,0.048344,0.057842,0.062843,0.072947,0.076433,0.08597,0.094973,0.10427,0.13558,0.18028]}]}}